cs.CR, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DS

The paper deals with the security protocol TLS, which falls under the category of cryptography and network security. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of theorem proving and higher-order logic, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the optional parts of the protocol and suggests minor changes, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the resources needed for verification are mentioned, which could relate to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
